'''Dino Entertainment''' was a [[Wikipedia:Germany|German]]-based publishing company responsible for printing the [[Wikipedia:German language|German]] translations of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' young reader novels and some comics. Dino was bought out by the [[Wikipedia:Panini Comics|Panini Group]] ([[Panini Verlag]]) in [[2003]]. After this, Panini kept using the name ''Dino'' as a label until early 2007, when all of Dino's Star Wars Publications were moved to Panini itself.

